  <walkingDescription><![CDATA[<p>There are a variety of walks for nature lovers which takes you through the picturesque Mediterranean scenery, passing vineyards and olive trees surrounded with the scent of lavender and rosemary bushes. Take an early evening walk along the 2km long promenade between Piran and Portoroz and admire the spectacular views following a stop for a glass of wine or coffee in one of Piran's cafés watching the sun set. Alternatively you can discover the sea-salt pans in Secovlje, Strunjan and FiesaLake. These are some of the highlights in this little fishing village of Piran, and town of Portoroz with its marina. You can also explore the nearby ancient Istrian settlements of Kostabona, Pomjan and Padna.</p>
